The start of the Fall Sports season is upon us, this is a friendly reminder that all spectators are required to follow the IESA & IHSA social distancing guidelines when attending both home and away contests. The guidelines are listed below:
• All fans must maintain 6 ft. social distancing at all times
• Fans must remain at least 30 ft. from the dugouts at all times
• Masks must be worn by spectators at all times
• Keep groupings in one area to under 50 people
Thank you in advance for your cooperation!

post_text:
The Regional Office of Education #13 Preschool for All program at South Central invites children who will be 3 years old on or before September 1, 2020 to sign up for a Fall Preschool screening for possible enrollment! Please contact Morgan Ice at mice@roe13.org to receive an online screening questionnaire or if you have any questions. An in person screening through KSED will take place at a later date.

Preschool morning and afternoon classes will attend school on an AB schedule. Half of the class on Monday/Wednesday and the other half on Tuesday/Thursday with Friday’s remote learning. Complete remote learning options are available for families that request them. Any child enrolled completely remote will still be enrolled in the PFA program and will be guaranteed a physical spot in the classroom if and when families choose to do so. We look forward to hearing from you!

post_text:
What: Grocery Assistance through P-EBT
Who?: ALL students of South Central CUSD #401 regardless of income *
When: Deadline to apply is June 30, 2020
How: Online at ABE.illinois.gov
Why: All students who would receive free meals at school are eligible for the benefit. Since South Central receives a CEP Grant in order to provide free breakfast and lunch to ALL students when school is in session, that means ALL students are eligible for the benefit.
DON'T DELAY!! JUNE 30, 2020, IS THE LAST CHANCE TO APPLY FOR THIS BENEFIT!!
* NOTE: Families currently receiving SNAP benefits have already received the benefit on their EBT card and do not need to apply.
More information is available online at:
(English version)
http://www.dhs.state.il.us/OneNetLibrary/27897/documents/Brochures/4980.pdf
(Spanish version)
http://www.dhs.state.il.us/OneNetLibrary/27897/documents/Brochures/4980S.pdf
and at
https://www.dhs.state.il.us/page.aspx?item=123700

We plan to throughly discuss E-learning/packets with the students on Monday 3/16 to provide as much insight and guidance as possible. More information will be provided as it is received.

post_text:
Cougar Announcements
March 10, 2020

A huge congratulations goes out to the Scholar Bowl team for an excellent season. The team lost to St. Anthony last night in the second round of regionals, but not before scoring 490 points in a win against Christ Our Rock.

FCCLA: Please sign up by Monday, March 23rd if you are participating in the cupcake wars. If we only have one group, we will not do it.

Thank you Student Council members for overseeing the blood drive. Thank you to the donors for you generous donations. Our drive collected a much needed 32 units! That donation can potentially help up to 96 people. Thank you all for supporting this public service through our school.

Any Seniors wanting to go to Springfield on the Lincoln trip please see Mr. Bridges

There is a mandatory NHS meeting tomorrow 3/11/2020 during homeroom.

Homeroom meeting today is Prom Committee, tomorrow is FCA leaders and Friday FCA

Today’s lunch is Fajita Nachos.

post_text:
ISBE ISSUES K-12 GUIDANCE ON THE NEW CORONA VIRUS

The Illinois State Board of Education has issued a document intended to help K-12 schools in preparing and handling potential cases of the 2019-N Corona Virus. According to the Illinois Department of Public Health, the health risks associated with the Corona Virus to the general public remain low. We have been advised to continue to operate as we normally would for cold and flu season. For more information please see the attached document.

Click http://www.dph.illinois.gov/sites/default/files/publications/2019-nCoV%20Guidance%20for%20K-12%20Schools%2002.19.2020%20IDPH.pdfto see the ISBE Guidance document.

Please share!!!

shared_text:
South Central Sports Boosters
January 10 at 10:20 AM ·

We are currently doing 2 big fundraisers right now with another one in the works. There is money to be made but to do this we need more volunteers!! If you would like to help raise money for our athletes, please contact the following people:

To help with the Queen of Hearts Fundraiser (which is a big time commitment for those who have been doing it!), please contact Kelisha VanSyoc Amos, Shari Kuhlman or Chris Kulhman.

To help sell raffle tickets for our Cougar Quilt, please contact Melissa Hilmes, Brittany Garrett or Donna Hall.

There is another fundraiser that we will hopefully be able to begin soon. For information about that, please contact Brandon Swartzlander.

For general information about the sports boosters, you can talk to any of us or message our page. We have some parents who will no longer be helping due to their kids graduating... we need parents of younger athletes to take over!

South Central Sports Boosters
December 12, 2019 at 10:51 AM ·

SOUTH CENTRAL SPORTS BOOSTERS IS HOSTING A FRESH/SOPH TOURNEY THIS SATURDAY, DECEMBER 14TH, AT SCHS. THE SCHEDULE IS AS FOLLOWS:

9 a.m. South Central vs Carlyle

10:15 a.m. Salem vs North Clay

11:30 a.m. Loser Game 1 vs Loser Game 2

12:45 p.m. Winner Game 1 vs Winner Game 2

All Day for Adults is $5.00 / All Day for Students is $2.00
Sports Passes WILL NOT be valid

Lunch / concessions will also be available for purchase.

Hope to see a lot of fans come out and support our younger players!!

post_text:
SCMS FALCON ANNOUNCEMENTS 12-3
BRITTANY GARRETT
TUESDAY, DECEMBER 03, 2019
Congrats to the Lady Falcon 8th grade Basketball team on their win in the first round of Regionals. They play again tonight at St. Anthony Grade School 6pm against Stew-Stras. Bracket can be found in Documents.

Falcon Basketball tonight (12/3) at home against Stew-Stras. 7th grade game begins at 6pm.

7th grade Falcon Basketball JHNTC Tourney Bracket can be found under Documents. Our first game is Friday, Dec. 6th at 6:45pm in Sigel.

SCMS Student Council is raising money to "Adopt a Family" program. Money will be accepted until Dec. 6th. Winning class will receive a HOMEWORK PASS!

Anyone interested in Scholar Bowl, please sign up in the office.

FCA will be meeting on Wednesday, December 4th 7:45am in the Computer Lab. Donuts, juice, & milk will be served. All students are welcome!
